[<p>The vote Friday followed a debate the day before on two drafts by civic groups: one to fully ban abortion and one to allow termination of pregnancy through its 12th week.</p>, <p>Poland\u2019s current law allows abortion through the pregnancy\u2019s 12th week if the woman\u2019s health or life is endangered, the pregnancy results from a crime, or if the fetus is irreparably damaged.</p>, <p>The lower house of parliament voted for its justice and human rights commission to analyze the draft of the total ban, and rejected the opposing proposal.</p>, <p>Efforts by anti-abortion groups have been heeded under Poland\u2019s conservative government that stresses respect for the Catholic Church.</p>]